(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Barre &ndash; Police in Vermont say a man has been accused of using a bow and arrow to shoot and kill a horse.Authorities say the 23-year-old mare named Bunny was fatally shot this month in Barre.Searchers discovered part of an arrow lying in a pasture. Another piece was found in the horse's stomach. Police say the bow and arrow were reported stolen from the owner's car.Police say 20-year-old Quinton Clayton was charged on Thursday with aggravated cruelty to animals and unlawful mischief. Police say he was wanted on an outstanding warrant for failing to appear in court on unrelated charges.It wasn't immediately known if he had a lawyer.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.